From: 3090 team <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: 2026-05-09
Subject: [PATCH] fused_moe_triton: detect already-presharded w2 and skip narrow

Fixes the CT-format MoE crash at TP=2 documented in 3090 README Known
Issues (also reproduced cross-stack on R9700 — see their README entry 8).

Repro: launch the qwen36 preset at TP=2 with the CT-format checkpoint:

    MODEL=$MODELS_DIR/hf-mattbucci/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-AWQ-CT \
    QUANT=compressed-tensors \
    ./scripts/launch.sh qwen36 --tp 2

Crashes during weight load:

    File "python/sglang/srt/layers/moe/fused_moe_triton/layer.py", line 537,
    in _load_w2
        loaded_weight = loaded_weight.narrow(
                        ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
    RuntimeError: start (4) + length (4) exceeds dimension size (4).

Root cause: the CT loader pre-shards w2 to per-rank size before invoking
the FusedMoE weight_loader (each rank gets its own slice from disk). The
loader still calls `loaded_weight.narrow(shard_dim, shard_size*tp_rank,
shard_size)` which on rank>0 walks past the end of the already-local-size
tensor. Native AWQ stores at full global size on disk, so the same narrow
correctly extracts the rank-r slice — that's why qwen36 TP=2 on the
native AWQ checkpoint works while the CT mirror crashes.

TP=1 is unaffected on either format because tp_rank=0 makes narrow a
no-op.

Fix: detect that loaded_weight is already at per-rank size
(loaded_weight.shape[shard_dim] == shard_size) and skip the narrow when
true. Native AWQ path retains the original narrow, CT path takes the
copy-through branch.

Verified 2026-05-09 on 3090 v0.5.11:

    qwen36 TP=2 / 256K + CT mirror: 4/4 PASS validator (137.4s) +
    decode 30.3-31.5 tok/s flat 1K-250K, within 1-3% of native AWQ
    TP=2 receipt (32.2-30.9 tok/s same context grid). CT is the
    calibration-clean variant (0/31010 audit-flagged scales) where
    native has 144 flagged.

Unblocks Suggested-next §A1 + §F3 (Qwen3.6-35B-A3B Docker rollout for
SWE-bench Lite at 256K).

diff --git a/python/sglang/srt/layers/moe/fused_moe_triton/layer.py b/python/sglang/srt/layers/moe/fused_moe_triton/layer.py
index f34ffc1..4854679 100644
--- a/python/sglang/srt/layers/moe/fused_moe_triton/layer.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/layers/moe/fused_moe_triton/layer.py
@@ -534,9 +534,18 @@ class FusedMoE(torch.nn.Module):
             if not is_bias and not self.use_presharded_weights:
                 if self.use_triton_kernels:
                     loaded_weight = loaded_weight.transpose(-2, -1)
-                loaded_weight = loaded_weight.narrow(
-                    shard_dim, shard_size * tp_rank, shard_size
-                )
+                # CT-format MoE checkpoints pre-shard w2 to per-rank size
+                # before invoking weight_loader (the CT loader does the
+                # global → per-rank slice on disk read). Native AWQ ships
+                # at full global size. Detect the already-presharded case
+                # and copy through unchanged; otherwise narrow as before.
+                # Without this, CT MoE at TP>=2 crashes with
+                # `start (S*r) + length (S) exceeds dimension size (S)`
+                # on rank>0 (patch 030 narrative).
+                if loaded_weight.shape[shard_dim] != shard_size:
+                    loaded_weight = loaded_weight.narrow(
+                        shard_dim, shard_size * tp_rank, shard_size
+                    )
 
         # w2, down_proj: Load into only logical weight of w2.
         expert_data.copy_(loaded_weight)
